= Symfony Shortcuts Plugin =

This plugin is basically what the title says, a library of symfony shortcuts. The syntax to many functions and objects in symfony can be long and tedious to type often, so these functions have been created so they can be used ANYWHERE in your application.

== Out of box shortcuts ==
{{{
<?php
sfContext(); // returns sfContext instance
sfController(); // returns sfController instance
sfUser(); // returns sfUser instance
isAuthenticated(); // returns true false if sfUser is authenticated
sfRequest(); // returns sfRequest instance
sfResponse(); // returns sfResponse instance
?>

More coming soon
}}}

== Auto Loading Your Custom Shortcuts ==

Create a file named myShortcuts.php in your project_dir/lib/myShortcuts.php, this will be autoloaded and the functions defined here will be available everywhere in your symfony application
